The paper deals with algorithms for the single-source shortest-path problem in weighted unit-disk graphs, which is a problem in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes algorithms that use data structures and techniques from algorithm design and analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper involves some combinatorial and discrete mathematics, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.DC (Discrete Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper proposes approximation algorithms, which could also make it relevant to cs.AL (Algorithms and Complexity).
